{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f2cf0291-9ca8-4d6f-abda-614f5d3838eb","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter editing, run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nCheck for any breaking changes in the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/) and update any NuGet packages that have new major versions targeting `net11.0`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ee17c06f-8500-4ffe-8631-eb15b2f689c9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore.","outputTokens":280,"requestId":"B00D:37A92F:C9C636:E9CD49:69F2B411"},"id":"f4bda88f-0034-41be-b7b3-a6b703cbe225","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:44:56.489Z","parentId":"077d8e22-2b13-47bb-a08d-da409a3cd74e"}
